{
  "doc_id": "42341",
  "text": "For a set of operons in E. coli, we did functional enrichment analysis of the corresponding genes with DAVID [CITATION_1] . Specifically, given a set of operons, their genes were picked from the DOOR2 database [CITATION_2] and submitted to DAVID as the input gene list with this genome as background genome. The p-values were calculated in terms of a Bonferroni-corrected modified Fisher's exact test under the null hypothesis that this set of genes was not enriched with certain biological functions.",
